cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) using pre-trained sentence-level contextual representations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and its intersection with computer science. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel structure for leveraging monolingual data, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses the Transformer model, which is a popular deep learning architecture, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on image captioning, which falls under the scope of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
